<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Rennes have informed Chelsea that they want over £30million if they are to sell goalkeeper Edouard Mendy in this transfer window.</p>

<p>Chelsea manager Frank Lampard is eager to bring the Senegal shot-stopper to Stamford Bridge, as reported by The Telegraph.</p>

<p>Lampard is unconvinced by Kepa Arrizabalaga, who has been unable to justify the £72million fee that Chelsea paid for him two years ago. </p>

<p>Rennes have informed Chelsea that goalkeeper Edouard Mendy will cost £30million</p>

<p>Mendy has kept 13 clean sheets in 34 appearances for Rennes since he joined the club last year.</p>

<p>There is a possibility that Kepa could stay at Chelsea but he would fall down the pecking order if Mendy arrives. </p>

<p>Willy Caballero is still at the club, but Lampard is eager to bring in a long-term solution to Chelsea's goalkeeping issue, with Mendy his preferred choice.</p>

<p>Chelsea manager Frank Lampard is looking to replace goalkeeper Kepa Arrizabalaga</p>

<p>Lampard has overseen a significant recruitment drive as Chelsea seek to improve their squad</p>

<p>Chelsea have undertaken a significant recruitment drive as they attempt to push on further.</p>

<p>Hakim Ziyech, Timo Werner, Ben Chilwell and Thiago Silva have all joined as Lampard has strengthened his side in various positions.</p>

<p>Bayer Leverkusen star Kai Havertz could be the next arrival at the club and there may well be further acquisitions beyond that.  </p>
